Problems in application which should be considered
  1>Maintainability
  2>Readebility
  3>Bugs

To tackle this SOLID principles were introduced

SOLID Principles:-

S(Single Responsibility Principle)
O(Open Close Principle)
L(Liskov Substitution Principle)
I(Interface Segrigation Principle)
D(Dependency Inversion Principle)

S->A class should handle only one thing/responsibility
O->A class should be open for extension but should be close for modification
L->
